alert_lib CHANGELOG
====================

- 1.0.5 | Mar 23 2026:

  [Change] README: restructure to rfxn documentation convention floor level;
      add numbered sections (## 1. through ## 12.), centered badge row with
      flat-square style, bold one-liner, copyright blockquote, ## Support section

- 1.0.5 | Mar 16 2026:

  [Fix] All rm -f calls use 'command rm -f' to bypass potential user aliases
      on target systems; 17 instances across all delivery and cleanup paths
  [Fix] _alert_slack_upload: JSON-escape $channels and $file_id in
      completeUploadExternal request body; prevents malformed JSON from
      channel names containing special characters
  [Fix] _alert_slack_post_message: replace awk -v with ENVIRON pattern for
      channel injection; prevents backslash interpretation in channel names
  [Fix] _alert_html_escape: use printf '%s' output (no trailing newline) to
      match _alert_json_escape, _alert_telegram_escape, _alert_slack_escape
  [New] _alert_deliver_email: validate non-empty recipient at function entry
  [New] _alert_slack_post_message: validate payload_file exists before
      processing; matches _alert_slack_upload validation pattern
  [New] Tests for telegram_document missing chat_id, Reply-To in text-sendmail
      fallback, empty email recipient validation, Slack channel JSON escaping,
      Slack payload_file guard, Slack channel backslash preservation (ENVIRON)
  [Change] README: add ALERT_EMAIL_REPLY_TO to environment variables table,
      add _alert_redact_url to API reference, update version badge and test
      counts

- 1.0.4 | Mar 11 2026:

  [Fix] _alert_slack_post_message, _alert_slack_upload: write Slack API token
      to a chmod 600 temp file and pass via curl -K to keep token out of
      /proc/PID/cmdline; Telegram already used this pattern; Slack now matches

- 1.0.3 | Mar 07 2026:

  [New] Template examples in examples/templates/ with working email (text
      and HTML), Slack (Block Kit JSON), Telegram (MarkdownV2), and Discord
      (embed JSON) templates using {{VAR}} token syntax
  [New] README: integration checklist, use cases, and troubleshooting sections
  [Fix] _alert_slack_post_message: replace sed s/// with awk to prevent crash
      when ALERT_SLACK_CHANNEL contains forward slash or ampersand
  [Fix] _alert_digest_flush: capture subshell exit code after flock timeout
      and propagate failure; previously returned 0 on lock timeout
  [Change] MIME boundary uses /dev/urandom-derived random suffix instead of
      $$ (PID) for improved uniqueness

- 1.0.2 | Mar 06 2026:
  [Fix] SMTP relay credentials no longer visible in process listing;
      _alert_email_relay uses curl -K config file (chmod 600, cleaned after
      use) instead of --user command-line argument; follows same security
      pattern as _alert_telegram_api
  [Fix] Webhook URLs containing embedded tokens (Slack incoming webhooks,
      Discord webhooks) redacted in _alert_curl_post error messages;
      new _alert_redact_url helper strips token portion from known webhook
      URL patterns before logging to stderr
  [Change] _alert_email_relay adds -s (silent) flag to curl for consistency
      with _alert_curl_post and _alert_telegram_api
  [New] Tests for SMTP config file credential hiding, URL redaction of
      Slack/Discord webhooks, and curl_post error message verification

- 1.0.1 | Mar 06 2026:
  [New] ALERT_EMAIL_REPLY_TO env var support in _alert_email_local (html/both
      sendmail paths) and _alert_deliver_email relay path; enables consuming
      projects to set custom Reply-To headers for panel email delivery
  [New] Subject CR/LF sanitization in _alert_deliver_email entry point to
      prevent email header injection; all consumers benefit automatically
  [New] Sendmail fallback for text format in _alert_email_local; when mail
      binary is not available, constructs RFC 822 message and delivers via
      sendmail with proper From/Subject/Reply-To headers
  [New] Tests for Reply-To header in local html, local both, and relay paths;
      tests for CR/LF stripping in local and relay delivery paths; test for
      text format sendmail fallback

- 1.0.0 | Mar 05 2026:
  [New] README.md with full API reference, environment variables,
      template system documentation, and usage examples
  [New] Digest/spool system: _alert_spool_append for timestamped entry
      accumulation under flock, _alert_digest_check for age-based flush
      triggering, _alert_digest_flush for atomic spool drain with
      consumer-provided callback; generalized from BFD with explicit
      spool_file arguments replacing env vars and callback pattern
      replacing hardcoded function calls
  [New] Test suite 07-digest.bats: 25 tests covering spool append,
      digest check, digest flush, callback invocation, epoch stripping,
      lock behavior, and full append-check-flush integration cycle
  [New] Discord delivery: webhook (_alert_discord_webhook) with HTTP 204
      empty-body success detection, multipart file upload
      (_alert_discord_upload) in single POST with payload_json + files[0];
      router _alert_deliver_discord with ALERT_DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL env var
  [New] Discord channel handler (_alert_handle_discord) with built-in
      channel registration (disabled by default)
  [New] Test suite 06-discord.bats: 22 tests covering webhook delivery,
      multipart upload, delivery router, handler, and channel registration
  [New] Telegram delivery: sendMessage (_alert_telegram_message) with
      MarkdownV2 parse mode, sendDocument (_alert_telegram_document) with
      file upload and optional caption; router _alert_deliver_telegram
      with env var config (ALERT_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, ALERT_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID)
  [New] Telegram API helper (_alert_telegram_api): shared curl -K config
      file pattern keeping bot token out of process listing (chmod 600
      temp file, rm after use); response validation with error extraction
  [New] Telegram channel handler (_alert_handle_telegram) with built-in
      channel registration (disabled by default)
  [New] Test suite 05-telegram.bats: 35 tests covering API helper security
      (token not in args, config file permissions, cleanup), sendMessage,
      sendDocument, delivery router, handler, and channel registration
  [New] Slack delivery: webhook (_alert_slack_webhook), bot API
      (_alert_slack_post_message), 3-step file upload (_alert_slack_upload);
      router _alert_deliver_slack with ALERT_SLACK_MODE webhook|bot
  [New] HTTP utility: _alert_curl_post shared POST helper with configurable
      timeouts (ALERT_CURL_TIMEOUT, ALERT_CURL_MAX_TIME), stderr capture,
      and error detail logging
  [New] URL validation: _alert_validate_url for http/https URL checking
  [New] Slack channel handler (_alert_handle_slack) with built-in channel
      registration (disabled by default)
  [New] Test suite 04-slack.bats: tests covering HTTP utilities, Slack
      webhook, bot API, 3-step upload, delivery router, handler, and
      channel registration
  [New] Test helper: alert_create_curl_mock and alert_create_curl_routing_mock
      for response-aware and multi-step API curl mocking
  [New] Channel registry: alert_channel_register, alert_channel_enable,
      alert_channel_disable, alert_channel_enabled with parallel indexed
      arrays and _alert_channel_find lookup helper
  [New] Multi-channel dispatch: alert_dispatch with per-channel template
      rendering (.text.tpl/.message.tpl/.html.tpl), custom.d/ override
      support, comma-separated channel filtering, and fault-tolerant
      dispatch (continues after individual channel failures)
  [New] Email channel handler: _alert_handle_email wrapper bridging
      standardized handler interface to _alert_deliver_email with
      ALERT_EMAIL_TO and ALERT_EMAIL_FORMAT env var config
  [New] Built-in email channel registration at source time (disabled
      by default; consumers enable via alert_channel_enable "email")
  [New] Test suite 03-registry.bats: 36 tests covering channel
      registration, enable/disable, dispatch loop, template rendering,
      channel filtering, error propagation, and temp file cleanup
  [New] MIME builder: _alert_build_mime (multipart/alternative with base64
      HTML part, ALERT_ boundary prefix, RFC 5321 compliant line lengths)
  [New] Email delivery: _alert_email_local (mail/sendmail with format-based
      routing and graceful fallback), _alert_email_relay (curl SMTP with
      TLS auto-detection and optional auth), _alert_deliver_email (router:
      ALERT_SMTP_RELAY → relay path, else → local MTA)
  [New] Test suite 02-email.bats: 29 tests covering MIME builder, local MTA,
      SMTP relay, delivery router, fallback chains, and error propagation
  [New] Mock binary infrastructure in alert-common.bash: alert_mock_setup and
      alert_create_mock for testing delivery functions without real binaries
  [New] Template engine: _alert_tpl_render (awk-based {{VAR}} substitution,
      mawk-compatible) and _alert_tpl_resolve (custom.d/ override resolution)
  [New] Escaping functions: _alert_html_escape (HTML entities via sed),
      _alert_json_escape (JSON string escaping via parameter expansion),
      _alert_telegram_escape (MarkdownV2 19-char set via sed),
      _alert_slack_escape (mrkdwn &amp; entity escaping via sed)
  [New] Test suite 01-core.bats: 33 tests covering all 6 functions with
      negative/false-positive tests for escape ordering and token matching
  [New] Project scaffolding: library skeleton, batsman test infrastructure,
      9-OS CI matrix, scaffold validation tests
